Definition: fill with apprehension or alarm
Example: cause to be unpleasantly surprised; I was horrified at the thought of being late for my interview; The news of the executions horrified us
Synonyms: noun, feeling, alarm, person, alarmist, appal, appall, horrify, horror, frighten, fill, with, apprehension, or, cause, to, be, unpleasantly, surprised, I, was, horrified, at, the, thought, of, being, late, for, my, interview, The, news, executions, us
Frame: 9,10
Category: verb.emotion
